@hmkem - wrong.  They turn off just fine.

But, there IS a problem with the Audio 1 track, described here as the AC-3 audio.  All vocals come from the Right channel, not Center.  And effects come from the Left channel.  It almost sounds as if the sound was encoded R to L instead of F to R.  Audio 1 playback tried using WMP, SMPlayer, Media Player Classic and through a WDTV Live Plus.  

The Audio 2 track, the AAC, works fine.
